HEADWORD: Epilepsy
<hw>Ep"i*lep`sy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>epilepsia</ets>, Gr. <?/ a seizure, the ⟦ldquo⟧falling
sickness,⟦rdquo⟧ fr. <?/ to take besides, seize, attack;
<grk>'epi`</grk> upon, besides + <?/ to take: cf. F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧pilepsie</ets>. Cf. <er>Catalepsy</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The ⟦ldquo⟧falling sickness,⟦rdquo⟧ so called
because the patient falls suddenly to the ground; a disease
characterized by paroxysms (or fits) occurring at interval and attended
by sudden loss of consciousness, and convulsive motions of the
muscles.</def> <rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

